news.title: SC directs Supertech to enter into contract within week with firm to demolish twin-towers
news.para: The NOIDA authority informed the bench that it has finalised the company Edifice Engineering for demolishing the twin towers in consultation with the Central Building Research Institute (CBRI) Roorkee.

news.title: China: Country Garden sees bonds slump
news.para: Last week was the worst on record for Country Garden's bonds and fresh falls of up to 17 points on Monday left most of its international market debt at 25-35 percent below its face value.

news.title: UltraTech announces Rs 965-crore capex for modernisation, doubling Birla White production capacity
news.para: The Aditya Birla Group company plans to increase the capacity of Birla White from the current 6.5 lakh tonnes per annum (LTPA) to 12.53 LTPA, UltraTech Cement said in a post-earnings statement.

news.title: UltraTech Cement's profit up 7.9% at Rs 1,710.14 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Revenue from operations rose by 5.89 per cent to Rs 12,984.93 crore during the quarter under review compared to Rs 12,262 crore in the corresponding period of the last fiscal, the company said in a BSE filing.

news.title: Mindspace REIT to raise up to Rs 500 crore through issue of NCDs
news.para: The executive committee of K Raheja Corp Investment Managers LLP, the manager to the REIT has approved the issue of listed, rated, secured, non-cumulative, taxable, transferable, redeemable NCDs by the REIT.

news.title: Ajmera Realty to invest Rs 900 crore to develop residential project in Mumbai
news.para: Ajmera Realty and Infra India estimates sales of Rs 1,500 crore from the project, which will comprise 540 residential flats and 18 retail shops.

news.title: Inaya Living buys South Mumbai bungalow Laburnum House for Rs 93 crore
news.para: The development company has bought the property through its parent Chandler & Price (India) that has paid stamp duty worth Rs 4.65 crore for the registration of the transaction.

news.title: Over 1,000 residential projects approved in Nashik during Aug-Dec 2021
news.para: Over 1,000 residential projects have been approved by the civic body between August and December 2021, while over 400 building plan proposals are still pending with the civic body for approval.

news.title: Kochi: No progress in project for P&T Colony residents
news.para: ​Though the piling works of the project was completed in August last year, not even the foundation works have started yet. The deadline is April 29 and authorities said that it would take more time than that.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh: Compounding relief to continue till Jan 31
news.para: Urban development and housing minister Bhupendra Singh has asked officials to conduct special campaign in all urban bodies to provide citizens with the benefit of relaxation in compounding given by the state government.

news.title: Colonies' information on Ludhiana civic body website hits font hurdle
news.para: ​Some of the information is in Punjabi fonts which are not readable for the devices that do not have those fonts. An RTI activist claimed that officials did this intentionally, so that actual information does not reach the masses.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Corporation identifies 700 defaulters owing tax dues above Rs 1 lakh
news.para: In the past two months, the corporation managed to collect around Rs 17 crore following the updation of tax database in all the wards.

news.title: Delhi model suggested for need-based changes in Chandigarh housing board
news.para: All the parties in attendance suggested that the Delhi need based changes pattern be taken as reference to regularisation of need based changes in CHB flats.

news.title: Mall owners likely to offer relief to retail stores, food outlets, multiplexes: SCAI
news.para: SCAI director Abhishek Bansal said some of the retailers have started approaching the property owners, raising their concerns over the impact on their business after the restrictions imposed by local authorities after a sudden surge in the pandemic cases.

news.title: Mumbai: Homebuyer fails to get possession, given Rs 2 crore
news.para: MahaRERA member Vijay Satbir Singh observed that the said MOU clearly provides that the home buyer agreed to purchase the said flat and the respondent agreed to sell the said flat to the complainant.
